RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COOL SPIRIT was bumped slightly by outside rival then pressed the pace from the two path, engaged the leader and took the lead near the three sixteenths pole, drew clear. ARKANSAS ZONG raced off the pace from the inside, skimmed the rail going into the stretch to prove second best. ADMIRAL RISTY chased the leaders from three wide and was along for show. INGLIS broke in slightly and bumped with inside rival, raced in the middle of the pack through the turn then moved out to four wide in upper stretch to improve his position. QUICK ZONG show good early speed to the turn then was headed at the quarter pole and matched strides with outside rival to the top of the stretch but tired. CLASSIC WARRIOR lacked room on the inside in the early stages of the race, saved ground but failed to menace. UNCLE CHAN had no early speed and went three wide on the turn but was not a factor. TOAST TO THE GIRLS raced in the middle of the pack and was not a threat. YO PLAY was off the pace to the seven sixteenths pole then dropped back. HOLIDAY FOREVER raced at near the back, fell and was vanned off. STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS POSTED INTO THE RUNNING NEAR THE THREE FURLONG MARKER, AFTER A REVIEW NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

ENTRY.NAME: Classic Warrior
ENTRY.COMMENT: lacked room, saved ground, failed to menace,

ENTRY.NAME: Arkansas Zong
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, skimmed rail, second best,

ENTRY.NAME: Cool Spirit
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped, pressed pace, led 3/16, drew clear,

ENTRY.NAME: Inglis
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, bumped, middle of pack, 4wupper, improved

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 95. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 37000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $15,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since October 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since September 29 Allowed 4 lbs. Cla iming Price $15,000 (Claiming Races Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OCEAN OF STORMS vied for the lead from the inside to the first turn then settled off the pace around the final turn, moved out to three wide in upper stretch and drew clear late. GRAVES MILL ROAD settled off the pace down the backstretch then moved between horses entering the final turn to engage the lead, took a brief lead at the top of the stretch but was outfinished. MINNESOTA MIRACLE went to the front to a pressured lead through the final turn and was overtaken at the eighth pole but held on for the show. COUSVINNYSACANUCK was allowed to settle down the backstretch then moved between horses mid way through the final turn and tipped out to four wide in upper stretch to be best of the rest. RUNNING LATE went four wide into the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack while racing three wide down the backstretch, moved out to five wide into the stretch to improve his position. DEEP STATE raced in the middle of the pack from the two path then dropped back near the three furlong marker. DREWPOWER remained back. PALATIAL TIMES raced off the pace from three wide through the final turn then appeared to take a back step, fell and was vanned off. STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS POSTED INTO THE RUNNING NEAR THE EIGHTH POLE, AFTER A REVIEW NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

ENTRY.NAME: Ocean of Storms
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied ins, settled off pace, 3w1/8, drew clear late

ENTRY.NAME: Graves Mill Road
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, between horses, brief lead, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Cousvinnysacanuck
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, between horses, 4wupper, best of rest

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 43000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $20,000 In Their Last Three Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOUDTHUNDRHEVYRAIN sprinted away from the gate to a challenged lead to the top of the stretch then drew clear and fended off the late run from outside rival. SECRET ROAD raced in the middle of the pack on the backstretch then made a four wide bid at the quarter pole but couldn't catch the winner. MATZOH BALL raced in the middle of the pack, moved between horses at the quarter pole but was no match for the top two. MIDNIGHT HALO raced near the pack to mid turn the moved up going five wide into upper stretch but was too late. JOSEPH H pressed the pace from the two path to the top of the stretch and tired. THEBOYZ SECRET showed no early speed then made a late three wide rally in the stretch. PATEK raced in the middle of the pack but was never a threat. FRAN'S STAR broke in at the start, raced near the back while saving ground to no avail. C F HENRY was forwardly placed on the inside then threw his head midway through the turn and dropped back. HIT THE BULLSEYE was off the pace early then slowly retreated.

ENTRY.NAME: Loudthundrhevyrain
ENTRY.COMMENT: challenged lead, drew clear, held on

ENTRY.NAME: Matzoh Ball
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, between 1/4, no match

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWO JET hustled away to a clear lead to the top of the stretch, fended off the challenge from GYPSYROSELEE at the top of the stretch and drew off. GYPSYROSELEE prompted the pace from the two path to the top of the stretch, gained slightly on the leader in upper stretch but couldn't catch and proved second best. DEAL ME A PENNY stalked the pace from three wide around the first turn then fell back and finished evenly. ADDI BUG was always back.
